Evaluation and monitoring purchase price variance to prevent errors in reporting and to challenge procurement team to optimise material cost
Supporting commercial team by providing standard cost on monthly basis to be used as a build-up for monthly financial planning
Preparation and submission of CSL overhead budget on quarterly and annual basis in line with communicated deadline
Balance sheet control, reconciliation and review of Material Price Variance (MPV), Landed Unit Cost (LUC), Post Goods Issue (PGI), inventory and other cost of sales (COGS) related issues
