JD 13:

Key Responsibilities

Strategic Planning & Investment
Lifecycle Cost Modelling: Build and maintain asset cost models incorporating depreciation, financing, and residual value assumptions to inform investment decisions and optimise total cost of ownership (TCO).
Asset Optimisation Analysis: Assess asset performance across utilisation, efficiency, and return metrics (ROIC, TCO, NPV) to identify opportunities for value improvement, redeployment, or divestment.
Investment & Divestment Support: Provide financial insight on asset transactions, quantifying the impact on cashflow, P&L, and capital efficiency.
Business Case Validation: Challenge financial and operational assumptions, ensure scenario alignment with LSAP strategy, and confirm cases are robust, defensible, and value accretive.

Commercial Execution & Governance
Asset Right Playbook Development: Define financial guidelines and structuring principles for asset procurement, ensuring consistent, value-driven decisions balancing cost, flexibility, and risk.
Deal Structuring & Commercial Alignment: Support commercial negotiations by reviewing financial terms, lease structures, and vendor economics to enable value-optimised outcomes.
Post-Deal Governance: Ensure that approved investment and lease terms are correctly reflected in financial systems and reported to key stakeholders.

Reporting & Ad-hoc Analysis
Prepare recurring management reports and dashboards summarising CAPEX, asset utilisation, return metrics, and investment pipeline.
Support consolidation and presentation of LSAP financials for monthly performance reviews (MPRs), forecasts, and ad-hoc analysis.
Contribute to continuous improvement of reporting tools, templates, and investment governance processes.
Undertake ad-hoc deep-dives and financial analysis on strategic priorities or performance issues as required.

